[{"location":"reference/","page":"Reference","title":"Reference","text":"CurrentModule = TwoBandHamiltonians","category":"page"},{"location":"reference/#Reference","page":"Reference","title":"Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"reference/#Index","page":"Reference","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"reference/","page":"Reference","title":"Reference","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"reference/#Docstrings","page":"Reference","title":"Docstrings","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"reference/","page":"Reference","title":"Reference","text":"Modules = [TwoBandHamiltonians]","category":"page"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.GappedDirac","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.GappedDirac","text":"GappedDirac{T<:Real} <: GeneralTwoBand{T}\n\nHolds the parameter of a dimensionless massive Dirac Hamiltonian.\n\nThe Hamiltonian reads \n\nhatH = k_xsigma_x + k_ysigma_y + msigma_z\n\nsuch that vech=k_xk_ym.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0)\nGappedDirac{Float64}(1.0)\n\nSee also\n\nGeneralTwoBand\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.GeneralTwoBand","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.GeneralTwoBand","text":"GeneralTwoBand{T} <: Hamiltonian{T}\n\nSupertype of all 2x2 Hamiltonians with all matrixelements via dispatch.\n\nIdea\n\nThe idea is that all Hamiltonians of the form\n\nhatH = vech(veck)cdotvecsigma\n\ncan be diagonalized analytically and hence most desired matrixelements such as velocities or dipoles can be expressed solely through \n\nvech(veck)=h_x(veck)h_y(veck)h_z(veck)\n\nand its derivatives with respect to k_mu. Any particular Hamiltonian deriving form GeneralTwoBand{T} must then only implement vech(veck) and its derivatives.\n\nSee also\n\nGappedDirac\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.UnitScaling","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.UnitScaling","text":"UnitScaling(timescale,lengthscale)\n\nRepresents a physical length- and time-scale used for non-dimensionalization of a system.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> using Unitful; us = UnitScaling(u\"1.0s\",u\"1.0m\")\nUnitScaling{Float64}(1.0e15, 1.0e9)\n\nFurther information\n\nSee here\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.dx_cc-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.dx_cc","text":"dx_cc(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the dipole operator matrix element ⟨ψ+|x|ψ+⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); dx_cc(h,1.0,-1.0)\n-0.10566243270259357\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.dx_cv-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.dx_cv","text":"dx_cv(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the dipole operator matrix element ⟨ψ+|x|ψ-⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); dx_cv(h,1.0,-1.0)\n-0.0610042339640731 - 0.22767090063073978im\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.dx_vc-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.dx_vc","text":"dx_vc(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the dipole operator matrix element ⟨ψ-|x|ψ+⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); dx_vc(h,1.0,-1.0)\n-0.0610042339640731 + 0.22767090063073978im\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.dx_vv-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.dx_vv","text":"dx_vv(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the dipole operator matrix element ⟨ψ-|x|ψ-⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); dx_vv(h,1.0,-1.0)\n0.10566243270259357\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.dy_cc-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.dy_cc","text":"dy_cc(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the dipole operator matrix element ⟨ψ+|y|ψ+⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); dy_cc(h,1.0,-1.0)\n-0.10566243270259357\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.dy_cv-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.dy_cv","text":"dy_cv(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the dipole operator matrix element ⟨ψ+|y|ψ-⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); dy_cv(h,1.0,-1.0)\n-0.22767090063073978 - 0.0610042339640731im\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.dy_vc-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.dy_vc","text":"dy_vc(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the dipole operator matrix element ⟨ψ-|y|ψ+⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); dy_vc(h,1.0,-1.0)\n-0.22767090063073978 + 0.0610042339640731im\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.dy_vv-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.dy_vv","text":"dy_vv(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the dipole operator matrix element ⟨ψ-|y|ψ-⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); dy_vv(h,1.0,-1.0)\n0.10566243270259357\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.hvec-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.hvec","text":"hvec(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns vech(veck) defining the Hamiltonian at veck=k_xk_y.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.vx_cc-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.vx_cc","text":"vx_cc(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the velocity operator matrix element ⟨ψ+|vx|ψ+⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); vx_cc(h,1.0,-1.0)\n0.5773502691896258\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.vx_cv-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.vx_cv","text":"vx_cv(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the velocity operator matrix element ⟨ψ+|vx|ψ-⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); vx_cv(h,1.0,-1.0)\n0.7886751345948129 - 0.21132486540518708im\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.vx_vc-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.vx_vc","text":"vx_vc(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the velocity operator matrix element ⟨ψ-|vx|ψ+⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); vx_vc(h,1.0,-1.0)\n0.7886751345948129 + 0.21132486540518708im\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.vx_vv-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.vx_vv","text":"vx_vv(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the velocity operator matrix element ⟨ψ-|vx|ψ-⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); vx_vv(h,1.0,-1.0)\n-0.5773502691896258\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.vy_cc-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.vy_cc","text":"vy_cc(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the velocity operator matrix element ⟨ψ+|vy|ψ+⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); vy_cc(h,1.0,-1.0)\n-0.5773502691896258\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.vy_cv-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.vy_cv","text":"vy_cv(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the velocity operator matrix element ⟨ψ+|vy|ψ-⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); vy_cv(h,1.0,-1.0)\n0.21132486540518708 - 0.7886751345948129im\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.vy_vc-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.vy_vc","text":"vy_vc(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the velocity operator matrix element ⟨ψ-|vy|ψ+⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); vy_vc(h,1.0,-1.0)\n0.21132486540518708 + 0.7886751345948129im\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.vy_vv-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.vy_vv","text":"vy_vv(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the velocity operator matrix element ⟨ψ-|vy|ψ-⟩ at veck=k_xk_y.\n\nExample\n\njulia> h = GappedDirac(1.0); vy_vv(h,1.0,-1.0)\n0.5773502691896258\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.Δϵ-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.Δϵ","text":"Δϵ(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the band energy (valence & conduction) difference at veck=k_xk_y.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwoBandHamiltonians.ϵ-Tuple{GeneralTwoBand, Any, Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians.ϵ","text":"ϵ(h,kx,ky)\n\nReturns the eigenenergy of the positive (conduction band) state at veck=k_xk_y.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#TwoBandHamiltonians","page":"Home","title":"TwoBandHamiltonians","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = TwoBandHamiltonians","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for TwoBandHamiltonians, a package that defines various operator matrix elements of 2x2 Hamiltonians via multiple-dispatch.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Idea","page":"Home","title":"Idea","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Consider Hamiltonians defined in k-space which are of the general form","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"hatH = vech(veck)cdotvecsigma","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Since this is a simple 2x2 matrix, one can express all desired operator matrix elements in terms of vech(veck) and its derivatives.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Below we list the functions implemented so far.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Eigenstate-basis","page":"Home","title":"Eigenstate basis","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"At the moment all matrix elements are given in the basis of the Hamiltonian's eigenstates describing valence- and conduction band states. Some matrix elements depend on the eigenstates' gauge, so we give the explicit form of the eigenstates used here in the following:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"hatHketpsi_mu = epsilon_muketpsi_mu","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"with","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"epsilon_mu(veck)equivepsilon_pm(veck)=pmvech(veck)equivpm h(veck)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"In sigma_z-standardbasis (muinuparrowdownarrow) the eigenstates read","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"braketmupsi_+ = frac1sqrth(h+h_z)beginpmatrix\n    h + h_zh_x + ih\n    _y\nendpmatrix","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"braketmupsi_- = frac1sqrth(h+h_z)beginpmatrix\n    -h_x + i h_yh + h_z\nendpmatrix","category":"page"},{"location":"#Contents","page":"Home","title":"Contents","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"#Index","page":"Home","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"}]
